---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Core, seed, and remove
white ribs from @red bell pepper{1}(cored and seeded) and @yellow bell pepper{1}(cored and seeded),
then thinly slice. Pick @cilantro{¼%ounce} leaves from stems. Finely chop leaves
and stems, keeping them separate from each other. Drain and rinse @black beans{1%box}.

On a #baking sheet{}, toss bell peppers, a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, and
a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until soft and browned, about
~{15%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #medium pot{} over medium heat. Add beans and stir
in @southwest spice blend{1%teaspoon}, cilantro stems, ¼ cup water, and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon}
(to taste). Season with salt and pepper. Bring to a simmer, then cover and cook
~{15%minutes}.

While beans cook, zest @lime{1}, then cut into halves. In a #small bowl{}, mix
together @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, a pinch of lime zest, and a squeeze of lime
(to taste). Season with salt and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortilla{4} in #foil{}. Place in oven to warm, about ~{5%minutes}.
> TIP: Alternatively, wrap tortillas in a damp paper towel and microwave on
> high until warm, about 30 seconds.

After beans have simmered, remove from heat and mash with a #fork{} or #potato masher{}
until mostly smooth.

Set up a station for making fajitas: place tortillas, beans, bell peppers, crema,
and cilantro leaves in individual serving plates or bowls and invite everyone
to assemble their own fajitas.